race.comment: VEGAS DANCER (11) finished second over 1600m at Swan Hill when resuming from a spell, beaten a nose. Easily the best run of her career, so no reason to think she won't improve further from the gun draw. RUSCELLO (3) missed the placings two runs back then improved last start but found one better over 2000m at Pakenham. Has the class to take this out. GOTTACOOKACURRY (6) finished out of the money on debut two starts back then was beaten 5 lengths when sixth in a 1411m contest at Seymour a month ago but gets blinkers here and can improve. SEA DANGER (4) was solid off a freshen last start at Donald and the rise in trip looks to suit again. Fitter now and is inching closer to his maiden victory.
